          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When measuring an angle in radians, π is equivalent to a half-turn.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This value is rounded toward zero to keep user computations with angles",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "from inadvertently ending up in the wrong quadrant. A type that conforms",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "FloatingPoint",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol provides the value for ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "pi",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " at its best",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "possible precision.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "print(Double.pi)",
            "// Prints \"3.14159265358979\""
          ],
